This is the roughly the equivalent of calling Animator.reverse(), except that it uses the same interpolation curve as animateIn(), rather than mirroring it. Also, like animateIn(), if the animation is currently running in the opposite direction, we reverse direction and animate for a correspondingly shorter duration.
